@page "/docs/motion-config"

<PageTitle>MotionConfig — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / <span>MotionConfig</span></div>
<h1>MotionConfig</h1>
<p><code>&lt;MotionConfig&gt;</code> sets default transition settings for all <code>&lt;Motion&gt;</code> descendants. Use it to apply consistent animation behaviour across sections of your app.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;MotionConfig Transition="@@(new TransitionConfig { Type = "spring", Stiffness = 200, Damping = 20 })"&gt;
    &lt;!-- All Motion children use spring by default --&gt;
    &lt;Motion Animate="@@(new AnimationProps { X = 100 })" /&gt;
    &lt;Motion Animate="@@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.2 })" /&gt;
&lt;/MotionConfig&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Reduce motion</h2>
<p>Respect the user's system preference for reduced motion with the <code>ReduceMotion</code> prop:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;MotionConfig ReduceMotion="@@preferReducedMotion"&gt;
    &lt;App /&gt;
&lt;/MotionConfig&gt;

@@code {
    // Read from JS: window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches
    bool preferReducedMotion = false;
}</code></pre>

<p>When <code>ReduceMotion</code> is true, all <code>&lt;Motion&gt;</code> children skip their animations and jump directly to their target state.</p>

<h2>MotionConfig reference</h2>
<table class="prop-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>Transition</td><td>TransitionConfig?</td><td>Default transition for all Motion descendants.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ReduceMotion</td><td>bool</td><td>Disable all animations for accessibility.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Children to configure.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Best practice:</strong> Wrap your entire app in a <code>&lt;MotionConfig&gt;</code> in your <code>MainLayout.razor</code> and check <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> via JS interop on first render.
</div>
